alternative, either. I can admit to this, too, because I would be curious

if he felt his credentials were being put under unnecessary scrutiny.

3. Colin Powell is full of shit, here, and the last election is proof of 
fraud. In Cleveland, Ohio and Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, not a single 
person voted for Mitt Romney. You're fucking telling me no one... not a 
single person in those 2 cities wanted to vote for Mitt Romney? Well, I 
know 4 people in Cleveland, Ohio still scratching their head here as to why 
their vote wasn't counted... and 3 in Philly, so, if Colin Powell does not 
believe voter fraud is real, that has to do with the fact that he is full 
of shit.

Prognosis: Colin Powell pwn'd himself by ignorance.

4. I knew junk science was going to make it in this list, so, fuck Global 
Warming, it's not science, it's junk science. Here's the deal, since no one 
has been on Venus, and certainly couldn't tell you what Venus was like 
millions of years ago, the biggest reason Venus can be pointed to for why 
climate change can be so drastic has everything to do with the fact that 
Venus has no trees on it. It has no vegetation on it, whatsoever, because 
if it did, the carbon dioxide level would find its way down... and I mean 
way down. A planet in the vicinity to the sun, and also does not have a 
magnetic field means it never had vegetation on it, because a prominence or 
solar flare would scorch any that tried growing there, if the solar wind 
didn't scorch it away first. It has a rather dense atmosphere, 
approximately 90 times what Earth's is, and as such will hold a shit load 
of heat in. This is comparing apples to watermelons. Any climate change we 
are experiencing is only moderately due to industrializing the world, the 
rest is due to solar activity, which, try as we might, we will never be 
able to control, only adapt to. The major fallacy here is not accepting 
that carbon dioxide cannot be converted back to Oxygen, which is absolutely 
bullshit, and that comparing Venus to Earth is even remotely possible is 
fucking bullshit.

Prognosis: The researcher was pwn'd before ever opening his mouth. Sucks to 
stand on the wrong side of science....

5. Wrong, Clinton holds that record. Overall, I guess your definition of

This is not about how smart a person is, it's about how pre-disposed we all 
can be to accept an irrational explanation instead of a rational one.  Our 
brains are built to make these associations even when there are none, and 
we typically learn to do this from childhood and are discouraged from ever 
questioning them.  So when we can't reason them out with absolute evidence 
the authority that we accepted in the past has a greater pull than 
contradictory information - even when it's not correct.  When we do reach a 
point where rationality replaces appeals to authority, it's still hard to 
let go of deeply held beliefs, but it's more rational to do so than not.

Feel free to justify your beliefs and keep them to yourself, or do yourself 
a big favor and let those beliefs go when you can't justify them.  Because 
if your standard of evidence is so low that such beliefs are justified to
